ygData.messageBody:
Also related to the dark circlet: I was there last night for about 5 hours with a friend of mine... Trez spawned 3 times during that period and had the circlet every time. The times he does not spawn a magician spawns in his place... I was a lvl 31 wizard and my partern was a lvl 39 druid, although the ele's and magicians are all green to me, and Trez himself was blue and goes down in two hits for 250 and one hit for 110. As for the trash magicians i kill them as soon as they spawn before they are allowed to summon there pet. Personally i think a lvl 30 wizard could hold the room solo, with minimum risk, but i liked having another person for security..

Wes Lobdell,

Trezdon is a Necromancer. If you speak with Ulan Meadowgreen (named Centaur in
S Karana that gives the quest), he will tell you a story about an evil Dark Elf
Necromancer, blah blah blah. The Dark Circlet is actually a pretty decent piece
of headgear but is NEC only. I think it's better than the Savants Cap but not
as good as the Runed Circlet. I'm sure after you get your greaves, if you're
ever back in Najena camping JBoots or something, pick up another Dark Circlet
and you might be able to sell it for a good buck.
